name: (4S)-4-hydroxy-2-oxoglutarate aldolase
comment: The enzyme from the bacterium Escherichia coli is specific for the (S) enantiomer. That enzyme is trifunctional, and also catalyses the reactions of EC 4.1.1.3, oxaloacetate decarboxylase and EC 4.1.2.14, 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-phosphogluconate aldolase. cf. EC 4.1.3.16, 4-hydroxy-2-oxoglutarate aldolase.

references.title: Purification, substrate specificity and binding, -decarboxylase activity, and other properties of Escherichia coli 2-keto-4-hydroxyglutarate aldolase.
Cloning, nucleotide sequence, overexpression, and inactivation of the Escherichia coli 2-keto-4-hydroxyglutarate aldolase gene.
